    <stitle>DOUBLE DIAPHRAGM ANCHORLOK SPRING BRAKE - INSTALL NEW SPRING BRAKE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>INSTALL NEW SPRING BRAKE</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>Before installing a new double diaphragm Anchorlok assembly, it is necessary to determine the
                        correct service push rod length to insure proper alignment and operation of spring brake.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Determine Push Rod Length</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To determine the correct service push rod length of the double diaphragm spring brake
                    assembly to be installed, measure dimension "B" (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0401912">Figure 12</hotlnk>). Subtract the setup stroke as listed in the Stroke
                    Values table with the spring brake fully caged.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0401912" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0401912" filename="../figg04/g0401912.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 12. Push Rod Length with Brakes Applied</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Setup stroke is only to establish push rod length.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
